Feature: (Tongue-Tying Curse)

    A curse that prevents certain information from being revealed by the
    individual upon whom the spell is placed. The curse manifests itself by
    causing the tongue to temporarily curl backwards upon itself.

    Pronunciation: - 
    Seen/mentioned:
        First mentioned as one of the spells in Curses and Counter-Curses.[PS
        Ch.5] Seen in Deathly Hallows as a deterrent to Snape, or any other
        unwanted visitor of Number 12 Grimmauld Place, from betraying their
        location to anyone else.
